The article discusses the recent shutdown of Apple Daily, an independent newspaper in Hong Kong, due to increasing repression from Beijing. The Chinese government has been arresting journalists, threatening media outlets, and implementing a National Security Law to suppress free speech. Independent media are crucial for holding leaders accountable and maintaining a free flow of information. The article calls on Beijing to stop targeting the press, release detained journalists and media executives, and respect the right to freedom of the press in Hong Kong. It also emphasizes the United States' unwavering support for the people of Hong Kong and those who advocate for basic freedoms.